metadata.name: Morning View
metadata.description:
A photograph of Mt. Bancroft towering above Loch Lomond at sunrise in the Colorado Rockies.

It was taken during an incredibly cold and windy morning. The entire process was a struggle, from hiking through knee deep snow in the dark, to being literally blown off my feet by the wind and taking shelter in a rock outcropping until sunrise. 

It was at that point, after all the struggle, I was gifted with the most majestic sunrise I had ever seen. Sharp rock faces gnawing on a cotton candy sky.

I feel this piece epitomizes the theme of my photography work. Solitude, The struggle of life way high up, and the beauty of the sunlit hills as the reward.
